<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="442" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Governor
                                    <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-07-27"><hi rend="italic">July 27,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I beg to thank your excellency for your telegram of yesterday advising me
                            of the steps taken in regard to the lynching of the Italians at
                            Tallulah. The President is gratified and entertains the earnest
                            confidence that nothing will be left undone to promote the ends of
                            justice and to subserve good international relations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>